UI/UX DESIGN PROMPT — Mapping Builder + Testing Workspace
🎯 Objective

Design a visual data mapping editor + execution testing environment that allows users to define, reorder, validate, and test transformation pipelines between a canonical schema (target) and source data with full step-level visibility and debugging.

The system is split into:

Upper Pane → Mapping Design Workspace
Lower Pane → Testing & Execution Workspace
🧱 1. PAGE LAYOUT
🔷 Upper Pane (Design Definition Section)

Split into 2 main regions:

🟦 Left Panel → Visual Mapping Builder (Tree + DnD Canvas)

This is a hierarchical drag-and-drop tree-based mapping editor.

🧩 Structure per Mapping Step (Node Group)

Each step is a composite draggable node containing 3 linked sections:

1. 🎯 Target (Canonical Schema Node)
Displays known canonical schema field
Rendered as a read-only node
Hierarchical tree structure (supports nested JSON paths)
Expand/collapse children
2. 🔁 Mapping Block (Core Logic Node)

Contains 3 clickable sub-elements:

Pre-Validation Name
Transformer Name
Post-Validation Name

Behavior:

Clicking each highlights corresponding configuration section in right panel
Hover shows tooltip preview of logic
Active state syncs with configuration form
3. 🎯 Target Field Node
Destination field path
Editable only in last active/new step
Must align with canonical schema structure
🧠 Node Behavior (IMPORTANT)
Entire step is a drag-and-drop unit
Dragging a parent node:
moves all children automatically
Supports:
collapse/expand subtree
tree indentation for hierarchy
Visual connectors show parent-child relationships
➕ Actions on each Step
➕ Add Mapping (adds new row at bottom)
🗑 Remove Step (with confirmation)
✏️ Only last step is editable in-place (others locked unless selected)
🔄 Duplicate step
⚠️ Highlight duplicate mappings (same source → target)
🔁 Sorting / DnD Rules
Drag reorder within same level
Drag across hierarchy to re-parent nodes
Auto-adjust child indentation
Maintain schema consistency on drop
🧠 Visual Enhancements
Tree-style indentation lines
Highlight active node (selected step)
Highlight invalid mappings in red
Highlight duplicate mappings in orange
Valid mapping = neutral/green border
🟨 Right Panel → Dynamic Configuration Form

This panel updates based on selected mapping step.

🧾 Fields
1. Mapping Type
dropdown:
field-map
transform
conditional
lookup
custom-js
aggregate
2. Source Field (Path Selector)
searchable dropdown
supports JSON tree expansion
autocomplete with fuzzy search
breadcrumb path display
3. Transformer
dropdown:
uppercase
lowercase
regex
concat
split
API lookup
custom
▶️ Play button:
executes transformation using sample input from Testing Pane
shows inline result preview
4. Target Field (Path Selector)
same behavior as source field
validates against canonical schema
highlights mismatches
5. Pre-Validation Script
dropdown OR custom script editor
supports validation logic before transformation
6. Post-Validation Script
runs after transformation
validates output shape/value
7. Fallback Value
used if transformation fails or validation fails
8. Preview Section
displays:
[source value] → [target value]
shows real-time evaluation based on Testing Pane input
🧠 Dynamic Behavior Rules
Changing any field updates preview instantly
Transformer selection dynamically changes available inputs
API lookup triggers async preview
Errors displayed inline under fields
🧪 2. LOWER PANE → TESTING WORKSPACE

Split into 2 panels:

🟦 Left → Source Input Data
JSON editor (editable)
supports:
schema validation
sample datasets
paste/upload JSON
optional saved test cases
🟩 Right → Target Output Data
Read-only JSON viewer
reflects execution result of mapping engine
🎯 Execution Behavior
“Run Mapping” triggers full pipeline execution
Step-by-step execution trace available
Each step shows:
input
output
status (success/fail)
🟢 Highlighting Rules
When "Play" is clicked on transformer:
affected target field turns green
successful transformation highlights path
Failed transformation:
red highlight + error tooltip
⚠️ Validation Feedback
Inline errors per step
Aggregate error summary panel
Missing fields flagged immediately
🔁 DnD in Testing Pane
Optional: reorder test cases
Optional: swap source/target views
🧠 3. CROSS-PANE BEHAVIOR (CRITICAL)
🔗 Sync rules
Selecting step (upper) → updates right config form
Running test (lower) → updates upper highlights
Clicking field in config → highlights node in tree
⚡ Live Execution Modes
Manual run (button)
Auto-run toggle
Step-level run (play per transformer)
🧪 Debug Mode

Must include:

step execution timeline
intermediate outputs per step
performance timing per node
🧩 4. ADVANCED REQUIREMENTS (MISSING BUT IMPORTANT)
🧠 Schema Intelligence
Auto-flatten JSON schema → path list
Smart path suggestions
Detect mismatched types
🔁 Versioning
Mapping version history
ability to compare mappings
🧬 Reusability
Save step templates
reuse transformer blocks
shared lookup configs
🧪 Test Case Management
Save multiple test inputs
Run regression across all mappings
Expected vs actual comparison (optional but powerful)
⚙️ Performance Considerations
debounce live preview
memoize schema parsing
cache API lookup responses
🧭 
Linear / tree-based list UI
Nested draggable components (e.g. dnd-kit)
Simple expand/collapse hierarchy
Right-side configuration panel


